# Valgrind suppressions for the libregnum test suite.
#
# This is a starter file. GLib/GObject one-time type-system and quark
# allocations are a known source of "still reachable" / benign definite
# leaks; those that surface repeatedly during real test runs should be
# added here. Only suppress things confirmed to be tooling/library noise --
# never suppress a real libregnum leak. See docs/building.org
# "Testing & Memory Checking".
#
# Run a single binary to triage, e.g.:
#   G_SLICE=always-malloc G_DEBUG=gc-friendly \
#     valgrind --leak-check=full --show-leak-kinds=definite \
#       --suppressions=tests/valgrind.supp build/debug/tests/test-registry --tap

# GLib type registration: GType tables and class caches are allocated once
# and intentionally kept for the process lifetime.
{
   glib-type-register-definite
   Memcheck:Leak
   match-leak-kinds: definite,possible
   ...
   fun:g_type_register_*
   ...
}
{
   glib-type-class-cache
   Memcheck:Leak
   match-leak-kinds: definite,possible
   ...
   fun:g_type_class_ref
   ...
}

# GLib quark allocation: quarks are interned and live for the process.
{
   glib-quark-intern
   Memcheck:Leak
   match-leak-kinds: definite,possible
   ...
   fun:quark_*
   ...
}

# LrgCrashReporter is a process-lifetime singleton obtained via
# lrg_crash_reporter_get_default(); it (and its init-time GHashTable) are
# intentionally never released. test-crash exercises it directly. This mirrors
# the `leak:lrg_crash_reporter_get_default` entry in tests/lsan.supp.
{
   lrg-crash-reporter-singleton
   Memcheck:Leak
   match-leak-kinds: definite,indirect,possible
   ...
   fun:lrg_crash_reporter_get_default
   ...
}